Description: Real-time Wayland screen mirroring to terminal
 Waytermirror provides real-time screen mirroring from Wayland to a terminal
 using Unicode braille characters, half-blocks, or ASCII. It includes
 bidirectional input forwarding, audio streaming via PipeWire, and optional
 NVIDIA CUDA acceleration.
 .
 Features include zooming, focus-follow, and support for multiple rendering
 and color modes.
